**Choose template-only** when the component has no reactive state, no computed values, no event handlers that need `this`, and no service injections.

**Decision criteria:**

| Need | Template-only | Class-based |
|---|---|---|
| Reactive `@tracked` state | ❌ | ✅ |
| Computed getters | ❌ | ✅ |
| Actions / event handlers | ❌ (use `(fn @arg)`) | ✅ |
| Service injection | ❌ | ✅ |
| ember-concurrency tasks | ❌ | ✅ |
| Only renders @args | ✅ | Can use, but overkill |

```gjs
// ✅ Template-only — pure presentation, no state
<template>
  <div class="flex items-center gap-2 p-3 bg-white rounded shadow">
    <img src={{@team.logo}} alt={{@team.name}} class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full" />
    <span class="font-semibold">{{@team.name}}</span>
    <span class="ml-auto text-2xl font-bold text-green-700">{{@team.score}}</span>
  </div>
</template>
```

```gjs
// ✅ Class-based — needs state
import Component from '@glimmer/component';
import { tracked } from '@glimmer/tracking';
import { action } from '@ember/object';

export default class RunEntry extends Component {
  @tracked runs = 0;
  @action increment() { this.runs++; }
  <template>
    <button type="button" {{on "click" this.increment}}>{{this.runs}}</button>
  </template>
}
```

**Rule:** Start with template-only. Add a class only when you need something that requires `this`.

**Use `@arg`** for simple scalar values (strings, numbers, booleans). **Use `{{yield}}`** when the parent needs to provide arbitrary HTML structure or other components.

```gjs
// ✅ @arg — right choice for simple strings
<template>
  <button type="button" class="btn" {{on "click" @onClick}}>
    {{@label}}
  </button>
</template>

// Usage: <MyButton @label="Submit Score" @onClick={{this.submit}} />
```

```gjs
// ✅ {{yield}} — right choice when parent provides structure
import Component from '@glimmer/component';

export default class AlertBox extends Component {
  <template>
    <div class="border-l-4 border-yellow-400 bg-yellow-50 p-4 rounded">
      <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
        <span class="text-yellow-600 mt-0.5">⚠️</span>
        <div class="flex-1">{{yield}}</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </template>
}

// Usage:
// <AlertBox>
//   <strong>Rain delay</strong>
//   <p class="text-sm mt-1">Play expected to resume at 3pm.</p>
// </AlertBox>
```

**Rule of thumb:** If the content is a primitive value → `@arg`. If the content is HTML with its own structure, links, or other components → `{{yield}}`.

**Use named blocks** when different regions of the component need different HTML structures. **Use multiple `@args`** when the values are primitives or single components.

```gjs
