This is the biggest shift from classic Ember. In .hbs files, any globally registered component could be used anywhere. In GJS, if it's not imported, it doesn't exist in the template's scope.

Curly syntax for component invocation `{{my-component}}` is not supported in GJS — use angle bracket syntax.

```gjs
// ❌ WRONG — curly component invocation (classic Ember style)
